A vote for me is a vote for your children, Health care for all, Quality Education and much needed Criminal Justice Reform!On Election Day 21 candidates are on the ballot seeking to send Senator John Cornyn home. He is facing 4 GOP opponents in the primary, 5 independents are on the ballot and a DOZEN Democrats are trying to take his job.  NDG reached to each of the Democratic party candidates and offered them an opportunity to share with our readers why they deserve your vote. Six candidates responded and you can read their answers in their own words. They are Michael Cooper, Amanda Edwards, Jack Foster, Jr., Victor Harris for U.S. Senate, Cristina Tzintzun Ramirez and Royce West. Despite multiple attempts for a response, the following candidates did not submit a completed survey: Chris Bell for US Senate, Annie "Mam√°" Garcia for U.S. Senate, Mary "MJ" Hegar, Serna Hernandez, D.R. Hunter, and Adrian Ocegueda (TexasReason).  Early voting continues from 7 a.m .to 7 p.m. through Friday, Feb. 28 with Election Day following on Tuesday, March 3.
